A- Pours a cloudy medium amber color with a 3/4 inch off-white head that retains well before becoming a thick ring around the edge of the glass and a full sheet of sheer surface foam.  Resilient lacing leaves small clots behind.
S- All citrus in the nose to the point that I get a vitamin C type note from it.  Also some dankness and grassiness though.
T- Pure juicy hop flavor with a bit of bitterness at first but it soon subsides and you're left with an orange creamsicle kind of aftertaste.  So incredibly drinkable for the ABV.  Rides that narrow line between juice drink and resiny hop bomb.  
M- Slightly sharp from the hops but also creamy.  Medium carbonation and a lightish body.
