4.14/5  rDev -6.1%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Bottled 4/29/2016. More IPAs!!!
Appearance - The appearance is hazy, but a much lighter hue of orange and yellow than previous renditions of Trillium IPAs. This is more of a pale, straw color than a deep orange. The middle of the glass where it is thickest glows darker than the rest, giving a nice sun-like appearance.
Aroma - The nose is subdued at times but is very much focused on the hops. This isn't an aggressive aroma, but what is there is pleasant. The Galaxy and Citra play nicely together, batting volleys of peach, lychee, and lemon back and off. There is a slight catty or skunky note at the very end.
Taste - The taste follows the aroma almost to a T. It's quite hoppy but without that raw harshness that a couple Trillium's exhibited. It's a little more balanced here than the aroma was, where a combination of fruits, pine resin, and even some slightly spicy flavors make there way here.
Mouthfeel - The mouthfeel is medium-bodied with somewhat low carbonation. Soft texture. Pretty much par for the course.
Closing Arguments - Overall, Vicinity is a nice beer but lurks within the weeds among Trillium's other offerings. I feel like other beers do what this one does in a better manner. Still a very tasty beer, though. 1,241 charactersnhindian, May 16, 2016
