4.52/5  rDev +2.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Apr 29 2016 bottle, opened on a metal door handle in a hotel room on May 4 2016
A - Beautiful new-East Coast body: hazy banana wheat.  Creamy white head pours a finger high in the hotel's lowball glass.  Nice retention and lace.  Extra points for looking good in a ridiculous glass.  Note to self, next time go downstairs and get proper glassware from the bar.
S - Trillium is to noses on IPA's what Mikkeller is to appearance on stouts - world class and remarkably consistent.  Cracking the cap filled the entire room with sweet tropical hops.  Rich cilantro, sage, and pine pop out once it hits the glass, with fruit notes of grapefruit pith, tangerine, pineapple, and orange rinds.
T - Smooth and fruity with a round, woody undertone.  Orange, tangerine and grapefruit up front with a silky smooth oat and malt center.  Pine, cilantro and soft, fresh wood slide seemlesly into the picture to round out the finish.
M - I'm honestly ambivalent on the mouthfeel.  Silky smooth and incredibly drinkable, but relatively light bodied for the style.  It's growing on me the more I drink it though.  
O - Stellar.  A fantastic example of a new-East Coast DIPA. 1,160 charactersvfgccp, May 05, 2016
