5/5  rDev +13.4%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Look - Had to make sure I actually poured the beer and not my children's orange/grapefruit juice. Murky, completely hazed....looks exactly like juice in the tulip. And a big pillowy white head that I'd lay on if I could. Amazing looking stuff! 
Smell -  As soon as I cracked the bomber the aroma smacks me in the face (in a good way). So freaking tropical. Pineapple, mango, guava, some citrus, some grapefruit, underlining dankness. Possibility the best smelling beer I've stuck my nose in yet. 
Taste - Follows the nose. A tropical juice bomb!! Pineapple, mango, lychee, citrus, grapefruit, some pithy type bitterness that suited my palate perfectly. 
Feel - Glorious mouthfeel. No clue where the 8.0% is. So easy drinking for a DIPA. 
Overall - This beer is perfect. Plain and simple. Hangs in there (if not better than) all of Treehouse's DIPAs. It's that good. The only downfall is I cant drink this everyday....;( 920 charactersTonyjenlasc, Oct 27, 2015
