4.52/5  rDev +2.5%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a 750 mL bottle into a Trillium tulip glass. Thanks Steve for hooking me up with this!
Pours a super hazy orange-yellow opaque body reminiscent of pineapple juice with a 2 finger white head that reduces slowly to leave heavy lacing and moderate retention. I can tell this is going to be one hoppy beer.
Huge citrus and tropical aromas.. grapefruit, pineapple, bursting passionfruit, oranges, some dankness and resin, maybe a very light hint of alcohol in the background. 
The taste follows the nose, lots of citrus, creamy malt backbone to compliment the big tropical hoppy notes.. the finish is slightly bitter and maybe a bit piney. Medium body,  medium-light carbonation. 
Another great one from Trillium. Can't go wrong with this brewery! 758 charactersgcamparone, Sep 26, 2015
