4.18/5  rDev -5.2%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25750 mL bottle, dated 8/25/15 poured into a tulip
Pours a hazy, golden yellow in color with 2 fingers of pillowy off white head that leaves moderate lacing and leaves just a thin cap. Aroma is predominantly hoppy with lots of grapefruit, tangerine, mango and lemon. There are also some "dank" notes that are present throughout but linger in the background. Taste is much like the aroma with a strong hoppy profile. Good mouthfeel with medium body and medium+carbonation. There is a bit of alcohol here but nothing overly hot. OWhile hops were the dominant aroma and flavor they were somewhat muted for a DIPA. I'm a fan of Trillium, especially their IPAs but I was a bit underwhelmed here. This is a solid DIPA and while I won't go as far as saying that I was disappointed I will say that I expected more. 805 charactersmnj21655, Sep 01, 2015
