4.79/5  rDev +8.6%look: 5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.75Poured into two Teku glasses. One for this guy, and one for this guy's hophead girlfriend.
A - Comes out looking like fresh-squeezed juice, somewhere between orange and grapefruit. Looks particularly ravishing when the light hits it. Hazy. Finger of head. Beautiful lacing.
N - A big blast of citrus, heavy on the grapefruit. Some light tropical tones within.
T - An earthy, citrus ball of wonders.
M - Soft, smooth. I've heard the word "pillowy" describing this beer's mouthfeel. I'll have to agree. It's so pleasant going down, you can damn near take big gulps and not notice you're messing with 8%.
