another review milestone.  22 oz bottle was poured into a tulip glass. 
Appearance:  A two finger head was poured that reduced to a puffy layer.  It is a hazy pale yellow color with some vision of anything.  Frothy lacing down the glass as the beer was drank. 
Smell:  Lemony, herbal, spicy, floral, citrus, tropical, pine, and grasy hops followed by toasted, bready, biscuity, pale, and caramel malts. 
Taste:  Love the lemon flavor, tropical notes, floral, grassy, herbal, piney, citrus, and tropical hops followed by toasted, bready, biscuity, cracker, and caramel malts.  Some chewiness and slight bitterness in the rear. 
Mouthfeel:  Smooth, medium to full bodied, a little chewy, slight bitterness, medium carbonation, and juicy.
