4.19/5  rDev -5%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25750 poured into a snifter. Another beer Gyoungit shared.
Superb frothy, chewy pale white head that shows excellent persistence. Lacing is everywhere. So scattered. Body is a cloudy orange and yellow mixture. Again, this looks like a pulpy juice. 4.25
A bit pissy on the nose with some passionfruit, pineapple and a slightly vegetal and floral aroma. 4
Fruit makes its way to the palate, passionfruit and mango, and a better dose of sweetness and malt than I've found in other similar beers. Melon and mango linger on my tongue with each sip. 4.25
The body feels a bit light for a DIPA, but the refreshing factor, juiciness, and medium carbonation all play well. The bitterness starts potently but mellows out quickly and lingers in a quiet sort of way with each sip. 4.25
Great aroma and flavor. I appreciate the consistency from nose to palate. It drinks very well too, almost dangerously so. Killing a 750 wouldn't be much of a problem. 943 charactersONovoMexicano, Apr 24, 2015
