Bottled 1/20/15, about 3 weeks ago
a - brew pours a cloudy orange brown with a generous frothy IPA head that hung out for ages and coated the glass in lace.
s - nose is all you could ask for in a IIPA, lush ripe citric fruit...really tropical, mango like even.  Just oozes juiciness.
t/m/o - surprisingly thin, some heat is noticeable, but all in all a super solid IIPA that leads with the tropical fruit advertised in the nose. Dangerously drinkable and one of the better new IIPA I have had in a long while.  Go get this one. It is VERY good. 628 characterscosmicevan, Feb 15, 2015
4.53/5  rDev +2.7%look: 5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Graffy, Feb 15, 2015
4.3/5  rDev -2.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Bottled 1/28/15, two weeks old or so.
A: Pours a very cloudy light orange. Tall, frothy offwhite head. Head retention is top notch and there are heavy walls of lacing as it slowly recedes.  
S: The nose on this is fantastic. Pungent, sharp grapefruit and orange peel. Hints of tropical fruit like pineapple primarily. A hint of some dank, resinous underbelly.  Wonderful.
T: More of the same. Loads of wonderful sweet and bitter citrus. Orange and grapefruit and pineapple all stand out once again. Sharp, biting flavors. A really bitter piney resin is in there too, mainly towards the finish. No real sign of malt, maybe some breadiness under all the hops but it's barely noticeable. Get hints of garlic/onion in the aftertaste, I'm guessing there's plenty of citra in here. 
M: Medium bodied, fairly smooth with a big hop bitterness punch. Lightly dry in the aftertaste.
O: Pretty serious DIPA. Fantastic if you like the fruitier hop varieties. Lots of hop complexity, lots of pungent flavors and aromas but the bitterness is contained well enough. Not teeth-chatteringly bitter but still plenty strong. Nice. 1,116 charactersDope, Feb 14, 2015
