A- Cloudy yellow-copper body, two finger fluffy white head that retains well, leaves an average amount of lacing on the glass. 
S- Resinous pine, grapefruit, citrus zest. Toasted bread. Minerals. 
F- Grapefruit, tangerines, orange peel, toasted bread, a bit of honey, minerals (presumably that house yeast) and a very bitter mix of pine and citrus on the backend. The bitterness seems to build up the more you drink this beer.
M- Medium bodied, a bit fluffy and feels soft yet substantial. Typical of Trillium's pale ales. Surprisingly bitter and resinous pine finish.
O- Very good and bitter DIPA, but not one of my favorites from this otherwise excellent brewery. 732 charactersStevedore, Feb 09, 2015
