4.63/5  rDev +5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a 750 mL bottle into a willibecher. This was bottled on 01/20/15, which was 4 days ago as of this review.
Appearance: Pours a hazy blonde, light amber and leaves a finger of white head, that slowly fades to a layer atop the beer. (4.5)
Smell: Lots of earthy tones, spruce, mangoes, pineapple. Quite expressive and mouth-watering. Definitely hop forward. (4.5)
Taste: Very tropical fruity taste - guava, pineapple, mango. Pretty juicy. Some grassy and earthy flavors as well as spruce.Very interesting and refreshing. Different from most of the IPA's out there for sure. (4.75)
Mouth-feel: Medium carbonation with a medium, creamy body. Works very well with the flavor profile (4.75)
Overall: A very tasty, fruity IPA. The aroma was on the lighter side but nice, and the taste burst with tropical flavors. Very drinkable and refreshing. (4.5) 858 charactersResuin, Jan 25, 2015
